Defines a single certificate saving profile.

Fields:

  • format (list[str])

  • key (bool)

  • name (str)

  • path (str | None)

  • serial (str)

field format: list[str] = ['pem']¶

List of certificate file formats to be saved

field key: bool = False¶

Defines whether the private key will be saved or not. If False, the private key will not be saved.

field name: str [Required]¶

Name for certificate and key files

field path: str | None = None¶

Extra path under the basepath for more flexible organization. If None, certificate will be saved in the basepath.

field serial: str [Required]¶

Certificate serial number

save(basepath: str)¶

Saves the certificate.

examples.generate_malformed.issue(cert: TestCert) → str¶

Issues certificate using the given certificate model.

Parameters:

cert (TestCert) – Certificate model to be used to generate the certificate.

Raises:

Exception – If the server response doesn’t contain the serial number.

Returns:

Certificate serial number

Return type:

str

examples.generate_malformed.load_and_save_cert(serial: str, path: str, format: list[str])¶

Loads certificate querying by serial number and saves the cert in the given formats to the given path.

Parameters:

  • serial (str) – Certificate serial number.

  • path (str) – Full path to the save location without the file extension.

  • format (list[str]) – List of formats. Allowed formats: “pem” and “der”.

examples.generate_malformed.load_and_save_key(serial: str, path: str)¶

Loads private key querying by serial number and saves the key to the given path.

Parameters:

  • serial (str) – Serial number of the associate certificate.

  • path (str) – Full path to the save location without the file extension.

3.1.2.3. Example for generating certificate profiles for base case¶

examples.generate_profiles.create_crypto_profile(crypto_profile: str, ca_url: str, headers: dict)¶

Generates example crypto profiles.

Parameters:

  • crypto_profile (str) – Name of the crypto profile. It is in the format of {key_algorithm}_{signature_hash}

  • ca_url (str) – URL of the CA server.

  • headers (dict) – Headers for authenticating endpoint in FastAPI.

examples.generate_profiles.create_entity_profiles(ocsp_url: str, ca_url: str, headers: dict)¶

Generates example entity profiles.

Parameters:

  • ocsp_url (str) – OCSP responder URL

  • ca_url (str) – URL of the CA server. Is also the base URL for CRLs.

  • headers (dict) – Headers for authenticating endpoint in FastAPI.
